-- Bahrain Financial Exchange Signs Derivative Licensing Agreement With FTSE
-- Shaji Mathew
-- 2010-07-27T08:38:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/bahrain-financial-exchange-signs-derivative-licensing-agreement-with-ftse.html

          
          
             The Bahrain Financial Exchange
signed a licensing agreement with FTSE Group to list, trade and
market derivatives products based on FTSEâ€™s regional and
international indices.  
 The derivatives will be based on FTSE Emerging, FTSE
Europe, FTSE BRIC 50, and FTSE Coast Kuwait 40, Bahrain
Financial Exchange said in an e-mailed statement today. The
exchange, owned by Financial Technologies (India) Ltd., plans to
start operations in October.  
